{
  "id": "019d2edb-1c69-7451-9eb2-716f27c62f48",
  "content": "## Cold Entry Brute-Force Search (Issue #21, PR #34)\n\nImplemented brute-force cosine similarity scan over Cold-tier entries stored in Redb. When `include_cold=true` is set on `RetrievalOpts`, the system scans Cold entries via Redb scope prefix scan, computes cosine similarity, and merges results with HNSW results by score.\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n- **Opt-in via `include_cold: bool`** (default false) — zero overhead for existing queries\n- **LiteStore-specific**: Uses `as_any().downcast_ref::<LiteStore>()` since cold scan is a LiteStore operation. Non-LiteStore backends log warning and skip.\n- **Deduplication**: Both VectorRetriever and GraphExpandRetriever deduplicate cold results against HNSW results by entry ID to prevent duplicates during tier transitions.\n- **Rayon parallelism**: `par_iter()` when cold_count > 1,000; sequential below that to avoid thread pool overhead.\n- **Embedding `.take()` not `.clone()`**: Avoids 3KB allocation per cold entry by moving embedding out of deserialized entry.\n- **Dimension validation**: Skips cold entries with mismatched embedding dimensions (protects against model changes).\n- **GraphExpandRetriever blending**: Cold entries get `(1-alpha) * cosine_score` with no graph proximity bonus, which is semantically correct.\n- **API exposure**: Wired through `corvia_search`, `corvia_context`, `corvia_ask` MCP tools and REST `/v1/search` endpoint.\n\n### Known Limitations (Future Optimization)\n- Scan cost is O(N_total_in_scope) not O(N_cold) because all entries are deserialized to check tier. A COLD_INDEX Redb table would make this O(N_cold).\n- Cosine similarity is scalar (no SIMD). Query embedding norm is recomputed per entry.\n- No automatic cold fallback when HNSW results are poor — currently purely opt-in.\n\n### Files Changed\n- `rag_types.rs`: `include_cold` on RetrievalOpts, `cold_scan_latency_ms`/`cold_results` on RetrievalMetrics\n- `lite_store.rs`: `scan_cold_entries()` method\n- `retriever.rs`: `merge_cold_results()` helper, integration in both retrievers, 6 new tests\n- `mcp.rs` / `rest.rs`: API parameter wiring\n- `Cargo.toml`: rayon dependency",
  "source_version": "mcp",
